{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6210", "repo": "rails", "body": "@jeremy @fxn I really like the idea of a `config/secrets` directory. However I still feel that it is best practice no matter what team size to keep dev environment configuration out of source control. \r\n\r\nWhat happens with a two or three person team and each has a different OS? Port settings, usernames, and socket configs could potentially be different and it should not be up to the project to tell the developer how to conform his/her development environment.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380c97bd3543c15100d190"}, "issue_id": 6210, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5628885", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6210#issuecomment-5628885", "updated_at": "2012-05-10T15:50:55Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito", "login": "mattpolito", "gravatar_id": "f9961873414a964cb8aa6d81aa2e2293", "html_url": "https://github.com/mattpolito", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/f9961873414a964cb8aa6d81aa2e2293?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc182f930a06317057d31c73bb2fedd4f.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 2145, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattpolito/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-05-10T15:50:55Z", "id": 5628885, "owner": "rails"}
